16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 3 O.S. 2021, Section 85, as last
18 amended by Section 1, Chapter 452, O.S.L. 2024 (3 O.S. Supp. 2024,
19 Section 85), is amended to read as follows:
20 Section 85. A. The Oklahoma Department of Aerospace and
21 Aeronautics and its Director acting under its authority is empowered
22 and directed to encourage, foster, and assist in the development of
23 aerospace and aeronautics in this state and to encourage the
24 establishment of airports and air navigation facilities. It shall
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB730 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 coop erate with and assist the federal government, the municipalities
2 of this state, and other persons in the development of aerospace and
3 aeronautics, and shall seek to coordinate the aeronautical
4 activities of these bodies and persons. Municipalities are
5 authorized to cooperate with the Department in the development of
6 aeronautics and aeronautical facilities in this state.
7 B. The Department may organize and administer an aerospace and
8 aviation education program in cooperation with the schools,
9 colleges, and for the general public, and may prepare and conduct
10 voluntary flight clinics for airmen and issue such bulletins and
11 publications as may be required. This program shall be known and
12 may be cited as the “AeroSPACE Program” or “Aero Student Pathways
13 for Aerospace Careers and Education”. This program shall be a
14 partnership with primary, secondary, career technology, and higher
15 education providers to respond to the workforce needs of the
16 aviation and aerospace industry by promoting and organizing quality
17 curriculum, enhanced classroom instruction, and research-based
18 educational programs. The AeroSPACE Program shall collaborate with
19 industry and act as the facilitator for the collection and sharing
20 of information, development and implementation of activities, and
21 the dissemination of resources concerning aerospace education with
22 the primary goal being to establish a common statewide strategy for
23 implementing aerospace educational curriculum initiatives to better
24 prepare students for an aviation and aerospace career. The Oklahoma
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB730 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 Aero nautics Commission may employ established program processes or
2 contract with other qualified entities to operate the AeroSPACE
3 Program. The Oklahoma Aeronautics Commission may accept funding
4 that includes, but is not limited to, donations, contractual
5 arrangements, in-kind services, federal or state appropriations, and
6 grants.
7 C. The Department shall assist in all aeronautical matters
8 related to emergency management actions in conformance with federal
9 directions and with the Emergency Operations Plan of the state.
10 D. The Department may establish air markers throughout the
11 state.
12 E. The Department may purchase and install roadside signs
13 directing highway traffic to airports, subject to approval of the
14 State Transportation Commission.
15 F. The Department shall:
16 1. Draft and recommend necessary legislation to advance the
17 interests of the state in aerospace and aeronautics;
18 2. Represent the state in aeronautical matters before federal
19 agencies and other state agencies; and
20 3. Participate as party plaintiff or defendant or as intervener
21 on behalf of the state or any municipality or citizen thereof in any
22 proceeding which involves the interest of the state in aerospace or
23 aeronautics.
24
