(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 G. 1. The Department shall develop and adopt a five-year
2 Airport Construction Program on an annual basis which lists federal
3 and state funding that the Department has available for the
4 development of airport infrastructure. In addition, the Department
5 shall adopt a statewide airport system plan on a regular basis which
6 details the twenty-year planning horizon for publicly owned, public-
7 use airports and sets the service level, role, and functional
8 classification of airports within the Oklahoma Airport System. The
9 system plan will be made available to the public and shall serve as
10 the Department’s official document which guides the programming of
11 public funds for airport infrastructure. An airport must be
12 included in the system plan to be eligible for funding.
13 2. The development of the five-year Airport Construction
14 Program shall begin with supporting and achieving the goals laid out
15 in the statewide airport system plan and will be guided by the air
16 transportation needs and priorities of airports within the system.
17 The basic goals within the system plan include, but are not limited
18 to, airport safety, security, infrastructure preservation and
19 sustainment, economic enhancement, capacity, meeting Federal
20 Aviation Administration (FAA) or Department standards, and pro-
21 growth development.
22 3. The Department shall involve public input during the
23 development of the five-year Airport Construction Program each year
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB730 SFLR Page 4
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 and coordinate and receive input from the airports within the
2 statewide airport system plan.
3 4. The Department shall set realistic project delivery
4 schedules across the five-year window of the Airport Construction
5 Program to maintain the integrity of the Program and to minimize air
6 transportation disruptions.
7 H. 1. The Department may, insofar as is reasonably possible,
8 make available its engineering and other technical services to any
9 municipality or person desiring them in connection with the
10 planning, acquisition, construction, improvement, maintenance, or
11 operation of airports or navigation facilities.
12 2. The Department may render financial assistance by grant or
13 loan or both to any municipality or municipalities acting jointly in
14 the planning, acquisition, construction, improvement, maintenance,
15 or operation of an airport owned or controlled, or to be owned or
16 controlled, by such municipality or municipalities, out of
17 appropriations or other monies made available by the Legislature for
18 such purposes. Such financial assistance may be furnished in
19 connection with federal or other financial aid for the same
20 purposes. A project must have been included in the five-year
21 Airport Construction Program and be at an airport that is included
22 in the most current version of the statewide airport system plan to
23 receive financial assistance.
